Usage: th-tool [--help] [--output=<path>] [--vars-dir=<path>] [--var-file=name=path]... [--var-res=name=path]... input-template-path...
A tool to process the input-templates with Thymeleaf
      input-template-path... the path to 'th-tool' template that going to be processed with 'th-tool' variables
      --help                 Display this help message.
      --output=<path>        output directory or a file (default: printing to the stadard output)
      --var-file=name=path   a pair of variable name and a path to the file with either '.json' or '.properties' extension,
                             which should be provided in format 'varName=<path-to-file/without/extension>.json'
                             or 'varName=<path-to-file/without/extension>.json'.
      --var-res=name=path    a pair of variable name and a classpath-resource with either '.json' or '.properties' extension,
                             which should be provided in format 'varName=<path-to-resource/without/extension>.json'
                             or 'varName=<path-to-resource/without/extension>.json'.
      --vars-dir=<path>      directory with files like 'var-XXX.json' and 'var-YYY.properties',
                             where XXX and YYY are going to be the names of corresponding 'th-tool' variables
                             (default: '.github/th-vars').
